^ &name mid - may &num the financial crisis 
^ at the end of &name , the country of &name was caught up in a financial crisis . 
^ it is unclear what exactly triggered it off , but rumours of bank closures spread quickly , and many people rushed to the banks to withdraw their savings . 
^ the banks found themselves running out of cash , and the government put a limit to the amount each individual or commercial company was allowed to withdraw . 
^ this in turn made it very difficult for companies to pay their employees . 
^ in addition , all credit cards and cheque transactions have been suspended , with only cash transactions being permitted . 
^ as the crisis continues with no end in sight , banks are now beginning to ask debtors to return the loans . 
^ many commercial companies , which have relied on such loans , now find themselves in an even more difficult situation . 
